  "prompt": "Who are some of the most beautiful Indian Women ever?",
  "response": "Beauty is subjective and varies across cultures, personal preferences, and eras. However, there are several Indian women who have been widely celebrated for their beauty, grace, and charisma. Here are some of the most iconic Indian women often regarded as exceptionally beautiful:\n\n### **Bollywood Actresses**\n1. **Aishwarya Rai Bachchan** \u2013 Often referred to as \"the most beautiful woman in the world,\" Aishwarya won Miss World in 1994 and has since become a global icon of beauty and elegance.\n2. **Madhubala** \u2013 Known as the \"Marilyn Monroe of Bollywood,\" Madhubala\u2019s timeless beauty and charm captivated the hearts of millions in the 1950s and 1960s.\n3. **Deepika Padukone** \u2013 With her tall frame, striking features, and poise, Deepika has become one of the most recognized faces in Indian cinema.\n4. **Priyanka Chopra Jonas** \u2013 A former Miss World, Priyanka is known for her versatility, confidence, and global appeal.\n5. **Sridevi** \u2013 One of Indian cinema\u2019s greatest actresses, Sridevi was celebrated for her beauty, grace, and talent.\n6. **Hema Malini** \u2013 Known as the \"Dream Girl,\" Hema Malini\u2019s beauty and elegance made her a Bollywood legend.\n7. **Kareena Kapoor Khan** \u2013 Renowned for her radiant skin and classic features, Kareena has been a style icon for decades.\n8. **Rekha** \u2013 A timeless beauty, Rekha\u2019s charm and allure have made her an enduring icon in Indian cinema.\n9. **Alia Bhatt** \u2013 Known for her youthful and versatile beauty, Alia has quickly become one of Bollywood\u2019s most beloved actresses.\n10. **Vyjayanthimala** \u2013 A legendary actress and classical dancer, Vyjayanthimala was known for her grace and beauty in the golden age of Indian cinema.\n\n### **Classic Beauties**\n1. **Waheeda Rehman** \u2013 A symbol of grace and elegance, Waheeda Rehman was one of the most celebrated actresses of her time.\n2. **Meena Kumari** \u2013 Known as the \"Tragedy Queen,\" Meena Kumari\u2019s delicate beauty and expressive eyes made her unforgettable.\n3. **Nargis** \u2013 One of the first leading ladies of Indian cinema, Nargis was celebrated for her natural beauty and acting prowess.\n\n### **Contemporary Icons**\n1. **Katrina Kaif** \u2013 Known for her stunning looks and flawless complexion, Katrina has been a Bollywood sensation for years.\n2. **Anushka Sharma** \u2013 With her natural elegance and girl-next-door charm, Anushka has become a beloved figure in Indian cinema.\n3. **Kangana Ranaut** \u2013 Renowned for her striking features and bold personality, Kangana has carved a unique niche in Bollywood.\n4. **Shraddha Kapoor** \u2013 Known for her youthful beauty and girl-next-door appeal, Shraddha has a massive fan following.\n\n### **Miss India & Miss Universe Winners**\n1. **Sushmita Sen** \u2013 The first Indian to win Miss Universe (1994), Sushmita\u2019s beauty and confidence have made her an enduring icon.\n2. **Lara Dutta** \u2013 Miss Universe 2000, Lara is known for her radiant beauty and successful career in Bollywood.\n3. **Manushi Chhillar** \u2013 Miss World 2017, Manushi has been celebrated for her traditional Indian beauty and intelligence.\n\n### **Sports and Other Fields**\n1. **Sania Mirza** \u2013 One of India\u2019s most successful tennis players, Sania is admired for her athleticism and grace.\n2. **Saina Nehwal** \u2013 A badminton champion, Saina\u2019s determination and charm have made her a role model for many.\n\nThese women represent a blend of talent, elegance, and timeless beauty, contributing to India\u2019s rich cultural and artistic legacy.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
